    "concept_group": "CVP",
    "concept": "Operating leverage (DOL) — Coffee Klatch",
    "question": "Coffee Klatch is an espresso stand in a downtown office building. The average selling price of a cup of coffee is $1.49 and the average variable expense per cup is $0.36. The average fixed expense per month is $1,300. 2,100 cups are sold each month on average. What is the operating leverage?",
    "options": [
      "A) 0.45",
      "B) 1.00",
      "C) 2.21",
      "D) 4.42"
    ],
    "answer": "C",
