    "question": "Channing Company has two divisions, S and T. The company's overall contribution margin ratio is 30% when sales in the two divisions total $750,000. If variable expenses are $450,000 in Division S, and if Division S's contribution margin ratio is 25%, then sales in Division T must be:",
